President Trump had a phone conversation with Abu Dhabi Crown Prince Sheikh Muhammad bin Zayid Al Nuhayyan of the United Arab Emirates. They discussed their strong partnership and their commitment to fight radical Islamic terrorism. They also talked about recent developments in the Middle East, such as the fight against ISIS and efforts to address the conflict in Yemen. The President suggested the idea of safe zones for refugees, and the Crown Prince agreed to support it. They emphasized their commitment to continue consulting on mutual concerns.